    "comment_id" : 3033384,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
    "body" : "Despite this I would much rather pass around a single object instance in my code, potentially with a getKey() method defined; e.g. I prefer: processProduct(Product) to processProduct(KeyValuePair&lt;Integer, Product&gt;) where the Integer is the product ID.  I agree that KeyValuePair (i.e. Map.Entry) or even a generic Pair is useful within a method logic but I don&#39;t like it to &quot;leak out&quot; as a return type or be supplied as a method parameter; e.g. I never pass around Map.Entry."
  }, {
