    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Android programmers could use <a href=\"http://developer.android.com/reference/org/apache/http/message/BasicNameValuePair.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\">BasicNameValuePair</a></p>\n\n<p><strong>Update:</strong></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://developer.android.com/reference/org/apache/http/message/BasicNameValuePair.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\">BasicNameValuePair</a> is now deprecated (API 22).\nUse <a href=\"http://developer.android.com/reference/android/util/Pair.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Pair</a> instead.</p>\n\n<p>Example usage:</p>\n\n<pre><code>Pair&lt;Integer, String&gt; simplePair = new Pair&lt;&gt;(42, \"Second\");\nInteger first = simplePair.first; // 42\nString second = simplePair.second; // \"Second\"\n</code></pre>\n"
