    "answer_id" : 41020140,
    "question_id" : 2973041,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>My favorite is </p>\n\n<pre><code>HashMap&lt;Type1, Type2&gt;\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>All you have to do is specify the datatype for the key for Type1 and the datatype for the value for Type2. It's the most common key-value object I've seen in Java.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/util/HashMap.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">https://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/util/HashMap.html</a></p>\n"
  }, {
