    "answer_id" : 59945161,
    "question_id" : 2973041,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>You can create your custom KeyValuePair class easily </p>\n\n<pre><code>public class Key&lt;K, V&gt;{\n\n    K key;\n    V value;\n\n    public Key() {\n\n    }\n\n    public Key(K key, V  value) {\n        this.key = key;\n        this.value = value;\n    }\n\n    public void setValue(V value) {\n        this.value = value;\n    }\n    public V getValue() {\n        return value;\n    }\n\n    public void setKey(K key) {\n        this.key = key;\n    }\n    public K getKey() {\n        return key;\n    }\n\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  } ],
